According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Aluminum Plates Market was valued at USD 36.24 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 40.45 billion in 2025 to USD 77.40 billion by 2032, registering a robust CAGR of 11.7% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing significant expansion as industries increasingly adopt lightweight, high-strength materials to improve energy efficiency, reduce carbon emissions, and enhance product performance. Aluminum plates continue to play a critical role across aerospace, automotive, construction, marine, defense, transportation, industrial machinery, and renewable energy applications due to their exceptional corrosion resistance, excellent strength-to-weight ratio, superior durability, and outstanding recyclability.
